revision.text:
{{one source|date=April 2011}}
The '''Annales Paulini''' is an [[List of English chronicles|English medieval chronicle]]. The Chronicles of St Paul's, as the Annales Paulini might be translated, is thought to have been written by a canon of [[St Paul's Cathedral]], London.  Because it covers the period of 1307-1341 it is invaluable for the history of [[Edward II of England|Edward II]]'s reign.  [[Adam Murimuth]] was a canon contemporaneously and originally from Oxford, thus intimating the author as his friend.<ref>Weir, A. ''Isabella She-wolf of France'', Cape, 2003; Notes</ref>

