enous Peoples: Representing Religion at Home and Abroad|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CyqY6VgmsgAC&pg=PA247|year=2005|publisher=University of Toronto Press|isbn=978-0-8020-3784-8|pages=247–}}</ref> * [[North Hills Museum]], [[Annapolis Royal, Nova Scotia|Granville Ferry]] <ref >{{cite web |url=http://museum.gov.ns.ca/nhm/ |title=North Hills |publisher=Official site }}</ref> * [[Perkins House Museum]], [[Liverpool, Nova Scotia|Liverpool]] * [[Prescott House Museum]], [[Starr's Point, Nova Scotia|Starrs Point]] * [[Ross Farm Museum]], [[New Ross, Nova Scotia|New Ross]] * [[Ross-Thomson House Museum]], [[Shelburne, Nova Scotia|Shelburne]] * [[Shand House Museum]], [[Windsor, Nova Scotia|Windsor]] * [[Sherbrooke Village]], [[Sherbrooke, Nova Scotia|Sherbrooke]]<ref name="DunlopScott2010">{{cite book|author1=Dale Dunlop|author2=Alison Scott|title=Exploring Nova Scotia: A Guide to 400+ Unique Adventures and Activities|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Kg3GDgAAQBAJ&pg=PA347|date=20 May 2010|publisher=Formac Publishing Company|isbn=978-0-88780-903-3|pages=329, 347}}</ref> * [[Sutherland Steam Mill Museum]], [[Tatamagouche, Nova Scotia|Denmark]] * [[Uniacke Estate Museum Park]], [[Mount Uniacke, Nova Scotia|Mount Uniacke]] * [[Wile Carding Mill]], [[Bridgewater, Nova Scotia|Bridgewater]]
