The '''''Rawalpindi Gazetteer''''' or [[Gazetteer]] of the [[Rawalpindi District]] 1893-94, is a comprehensive geographical, economic, social and cultural catalogue of Rawalpindi District. It was compiled and published in 1895 during the [[British Raj|British period]].

With 268 pages it gives an interesting picture of that period. [[Attock District]] is also included in it as it was part of Rawalpindi District. This gazetteer is part of a series district [[gazetteer]]s published in [[British India]].

